      "writtenOn": "2026-03-30T08:33:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "cnat_add_trace() is called from cnat_sub callbacks, which run after cnat_lookup_create_or_return(). That function starts with: vnet_buffer2 (b)-\u003esession.flags \u003d 0;\nThis unconditionally clears all flags including HAS_SCOPE. So when cnat_add_trace() runs and evaluates cnat_scope_id(b), the flag is gone and it always returns 0. The trace will always show lookup_context_id \u003d fib_index, never the actual scope_id that was used for the lookup. The trace is misleading/broken for scoped packets.",
      "revId": "2359c3a2e98ce1d1e3324c17dd7b83f67a098e29",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
